    <section id="survival" class="code-card">
      <h2>2. Kaplan-Meier Survival Analysis</h2>
      <p>
        <strong>Introduction:</strong> This example performs a simple Kaplan-Meier survival analysis and plots
        survival curves for two patient groups. It is commonly used in TCGA-based prognostic studies.
      </p>
      <div class="code-meta">
        <span class="tag">R</span>
        <span class="tag">survival</span>
        <span class="tag">TCGA</span>
      </div>
      <pre><code>library(survival)
library(survminer)

clinical <- read.csv("clinical_data.csv")
fit <- survfit(Surv(time, status) ~ group, data = clinical)

ggsurvplot(
  fit,
  data = clinical,
  pval = TRUE,
  risk.table = TRUE,
  conf.int = FALSE
)</code></pre>
