    <section id="enrichment" class="code-card">
      <h2>3. GO / KEGG Functional Enrichment</h2>
      <p>
        <strong>Introduction:</strong> This section shows a basic enrichment workflow using clusterProfiler.
        It helps interpret differentially expressed genes by mapping them to biological processes and pathways.
      </p>
      <div class="code-meta">
        <span class="tag">R</span>
        <span class="tag">clusterProfiler</span>
        <span class="tag">GO/KEGG</span>
      </div>
      <pre><code>library(clusterProfiler)
library(org.Hs.eg.db)

genes <- c("7157", "5290", "7422")

ego <- enrichGO(
  gene = genes,
  OrgDb = org.Hs.eg.db,
  keyType = "ENTREZID",
  ont = "BP",
  pAdjustMethod = "BH",
  qvalueCutoff = 0.05
)

head(as.data.frame(ego))</code></pre>
